03931 /****************************************************************************
03932  *          DataSet Converters and Loaders.                                 *
03933  *                                                                          *
03934  * A Converter is an addon that connects to tecplot in a way such that      *
03935  * tecplot uses it's own file/io dialogs to read the non-Tecplot data into  *
03936  * tecplot and the converter is a simple function that only knows how       *
03937  * to convert from it's own data format into tecplot's binary format.       *
03938  *                                                                          *
03939  * Converters are registered with tecplot by calling:                       *
03940  *                                                                          *
03941  *              TecUtilImportAddConverter()                                 *
03942  *                                                                          *
03943  * An loader works like this:                                               *
03944  *     - TecUtilMenuAddOption() is called to register a callback            *
03945  *       (most often used to bring up a dialog) to the loader addon         *
03946  *                                                                          *
03947  *     - The loader registers itself with tecplot by calling                *
03948  *       TecUtilImportAddLoader()                                           *
03949  *                                                                          *
03950  *     When a request is made to use the loader function:                   *
03951  *                                                                          *
03952  *        - The loader creates a new dataset and loads the data into        *
03953  *          tecplot by hand.                                                *
03954  *                                                                          *
03955  *        - The loader then calls TecUtilImportSetLoaderInstr()             *
03956  *          to assign the specific instructions needed to load the data     *
03957  *          into the current dataset. These instructions will be included   *
03958  *          in any layout files written out.                                *
03959  ****************************************************************************/
04022 Boolean_t TecUtilImportAddConverter(DataSetConverter_pf ConverterCallback,
04023                                                           const char         *ConverterName,
04024                                                           const char         *FNameExtension);
04025
